# Project

## Description

- Project defines Firebase Functions that are deployed on NodeJS v20
- Project uses Typescript as a main language

## Structure

- Main source code is organized in `src/` directory with the following structure:
  - `src/index.ts` - Main entry point that exports all Firebase Functions
  - `src/functions/` - Individual Firebase Function implementations
  - `src/services/` - Business logic services (e.g., notification service)
  - `src/utils/` - Utility functions (email, date utilities)
  - `src/models/` - TypeScript interfaces and types
  - `src/config/` - Configuration files (Firebase config)
- `lib/` - Compiled JavaScript output from TypeScript build
- `build/` - Build artifacts directory
- `seed/` - Database seeding scripts
- `features/` - Feature documentation and specifications

## Dependencies
- Project uses NodeJS v20. Use only compatible functions
- Project depends on Firebse libraries with following versions. Use only compatible functions.
  - "firebase-admin": "^13.1.0",
  - "firebase-functions": "^6.3.2",
  - "firebase-tools": "^13.31.1"